DESCRIPTION
  The set builtin sets the shell options and the positional parameters.

SYNOPSIS
  set [-abefhkmnuvxBCEPTARWISG] [+abefhkmnuvxBCEPTARWISG] [-o name] [+o name] [--options] [--] [arg ...]

OPTIONS
      --help              Display help.
      --options           Display every option with its current state and
                          description.
  -M, --mood=<...>        Set the runtime mood to shit, bash, or sh, or print it
                          with no value.
  -L, --init-moods=<.., ..>
                          Source the startup files for the listed moods, or
                          print the loaded ones with no value.
OPTION SWITCHES
  A letter after a minus enables the option and after a plus disables it.
  -o NAME and +o NAME do the same by long name.

  -a  allexport, export-all         Mark every assigned variable for the environment.
  -b  notify                        Report a background job's completion immediately when it finishes.
  -e  errexit, error-exit           Exit on the first command that fails.
  -f  noglob, no-glob               Disable pathname expansion.
  -h  hashall                       Retain command hashing mode for compatible option queries.
  -k  keyword                       Retain keyword assignment mode for compatible option queries.
  -m  monitor                       Run background jobs in their own process group with notifications.
  -n  noexec, no-exec               Read and parse commands but do not run them.
  -u  nounset, no-unset             Treat an unset variable as an error.
  -v  verbose                       Write input to standard error as it is read.
  -x  xtrace                        Print each command after expansion before it runs.
  -B  braceexpand                   Enable brace expansion.
  -C  noclobber, no-clobber         Refuse to overwrite an existing file through '>'.
  -E  errtrace                      Retain ERR trap inheritance mode for compatible option queries.
  -P  physical                      Resolve symbolic links while changing directories.
  -T  functrace                     Retain DEBUG and RETURN inheritance mode for compatible option queries.
      pipefail                      Report a pipeline's status as the rightmost stage that failed.
      failglob                      Fail a command whose glob matches nothing.
      shitbox                       Resolve the bundled shitbox utility names directly as commands.
      vi                            Use vi-style command-line editing.
      emacs                         Use emacs-style command-line editing.
      posix                         Switch to the bash posix mood.
  -A  show-ast                      Print the AST before each command runs.
  -R  show-lexed-words              Print the escape bitmap after each parse.
      show-exit-code                Print the exit code after each command.
  -W  force-warnings                Report strict runtime errors as warnings and continue.
  -I  mimicry                       Mimic the shell named by a script's shebang.
      force-diagnostics             Run the analysis stage before each chunk.
  -S  show-stats                    Print evaluation statistics after each run.
      no-diagnostics                Skip the analysis stage before each chunk runs.
  -G  show-memory                   Print a granular memory report at exit.
      login                         Whether the shell started as a login shell, fixed at startup.
      rcfile                        Whether a custom rc file was named at startup, fixed at startup.

  The -o long names:
    allexport, export-all, notify, errexit, error-exit, noglob, no-glob,
    hashall, keyword, monitor, noexec, no-exec, nounset, no-unset, verbose,
    xtrace, braceexpand, noclobber, no-clobber, errtrace, physical, functrace,
    pipefail, failglob, shitbox, vi, emacs, posix, show-ast, show-lexed-words,
    show-exit-code, force-warnings, mimicry, force-diagnostics, show-stats,
    no-diagnostics, show-memory, login, rcfile

rc=0
